<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7844101-robyn"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1444758942i/7844101._UX100_CR0,38,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7844101-robyn">Robyn</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes! The two of them are maddeningly annoying. I don&apos;t find Bree as bad in this book because she doesn&apos;t seem to really do anything here other than br<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes! The two of them are maddeningly annoying. I don't find Bree as bad in this book because she doesn't seem to really do anything here other than breastfeed and go on about her swollen breasts but in the last book I wanted to shake her senseless for her rampant and repeated stupidity. I mean really, who in their right mind walks unaccompanied into the lair of a big, bad and clearly rapey pirate and expects to come out unscathed?? *grinds teeth* <br /><br />As for Roger, for a man that suffers long and repeated hardships all he seems to give a crap about is boning Bree. It's literally all he ever thinks about. He seems to have no other character traits other than the fact that he sings and is too unskilled to live in the 1700s. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
