<span id="freeTextContainer7985483590332030650">Second read- 2021<br/>Reading along with the show but I fell behind— forgot how massive (but wonderfully written) these books are. Definitely have to finish this one and read the next to catch up... winter is a great time for big books!! <br/><br/><br/>First read- 2008<br/>Although I really do love this series-- but book 5 seemed to go on and on and on without really moving the story forward that much... certainly not 1,000 plus pages worth. That said, Gabaldon is a master at weaving characters, historical fiction detai</span>
  <span id="freeText7985483590332030650" style="display:none">Second read- 2021<br />Reading along with the show but I fell behind— forgot how massive (but wonderfully written) these books are. Definitely have to finish this one and read the next to catch up... winter is a great time for big books!! <br /><br /><br />First read- 2008<br />Although I really do love this series-- but book 5 seemed to go on and on and on without really moving the story forward that much... certainly not 1,000 plus pages worth. That said, Gabaldon is a master at weaving characters, historical fiction details galore and yet gives you just enough to want to read more.<br /><br />Looking forward to the next installment-- just hope it is a little less heavy on the colonial life details. I know more than I ever wanted to know about changing diapers and gutting animals in pre-revolutionary America.</span>
